<br>
I tend to judge according to effective tax rates. <br>
<br>
I tend to think that if you have more than 70% of the taxpaying population(35% on each side of the median--fyi, using the mean is wrong with societies where you have a skewed distribution of income) effectively taxed &gt; 45% then Gov't is too big and\or maldistributed in it's benefit schema AND it's depressing economic incentive that you should be promoting.<br>
